response: "{ \"title\": \"Find the Sum of Squares (Hard)\", \"description\": \"Write a function `find_sum_of_squares(n)` that finds the sum of squares of first n natural numbers.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef find_sum_of_squares(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer representing the number of natural numbers to sum up their squares.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- An integer representing the sum of squares of first n natural numbers.\\n\", \"code\": \"def find_sum_of_squares(n: int) -> int:\\n    return (n * (n + 1) * (2 * n + 1)) // 6\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert find_sum_of_squares(5) == 55\", \"assert find_sum_of_squares(7) == 91\", \"assert find_sum_of_squares(10) == 385\"] }"
